{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.18",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 18,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 18 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:1",
      "text": "He who is estranged seeks pretexts to break out against all sound judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:2",
      "text": "A fool takes no pleasure in understanding, but only in expressing his opinion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:3",
      "text": "When wickedness comes, contempt comes also; and with dishonor comes disgrace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:4",
      "text": "The words of a man's mouth are deep waters; the fountain of wisdom is a gushing stream.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:5",
      "text": "It is not good to be partial to a wicked man, or to deprive a righteous man of justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:6",
      "text": "A fool's lips bring strife, and his mouth invites a flogging.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:7",
      "text": "A fool's mouth is his ruin, and his lips are a snare to himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:8",
      "text": "The words of a whisperer are like delicious morsels; they go down into the inner parts of the body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:9",
      "text": "He who is slack in his work is a brother to him who destroys.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:10",
      "text": "The name of the Lord is a strong tower; the righteous man runs into it and is safe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:11",
      "text": "A rich man's wealth is his strong city, and like a high wall protecting him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:12",
      "text": "Before destruction a man's heart is haughty, but humility goes before honor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:13",
      "text": "If one gives answer before he hears, it is his folly and shame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:14",
      "text": "A man's spirit will endure sickness; but a broken spirit who can bear?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:15",
      "text": "An intelligent mind acquires knowledge, and the ear of the wise seeks knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:16",
      "text": "A man's gift makes room for him and brings him before great men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:17",
      "text": "He who states his case first seems right, until the other comes and examines him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:18",
      "text": "The lot puts an end to disputes and decides between powerful contenders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:19",
      "text": "A brother helped is like a strong city, but quarreling is like the bars of a castle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:20",
      "text": "From the fruit of his mouth a man is satisfied; he is satisfied by the yield of his lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:21",
      "text": "Death and life are in the power of the tongue, and those who love it will eat its fruits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:22",
      "text": "He who finds a wife finds a good thing, and obtains favor from the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:23",
      "text": "The poor use entreaties, but the rich answer roughly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.18.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:24",
      "text": "There are friends who pretend to be friends, but there is a friend who sticks closer than a brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
